name: Oakland basketball
summary: In the first round of the 2024 NCAA Tournament, No. 14 seed Oakland University basketball team made history by defeating No. 3 seed Kentucky in a stunning upset. Star player Jack Gohlke made 10 three-pointers, leading the Grizzlies to victory. Despite their upset win, Oakland's journey ended in the second round with a loss to No. 11 seed NC State in overtime. Gohlke's performance put Oakland on the national map and highlighted Kentucky's struggles in March Madness. The Grizzlies' victory against Kentucky was considered one of the biggest upsets in the tournament's history.

name: National Puppy Day
summary: National Puppy Day is celebrated on March 23rd and is a time to recognize and appreciate the joy that puppies bring into our lives. This year, pet owners are being warned to be cautious when bringing a puppy home, as some unscrupulous breeders may try to take advantage of the increased demand for puppies on this day. To avoid this, it is important to do your research and find a reputable breeder or adoption agency. In addition to warnings for pet owners, there are also many celebrations and events taking place across the country to honor puppies. ABC7 is hosting an adoption event where people can meet and adopt puppies, while the Daytona Beach News-Journal is providing tips on how to celebrate the day, including popular puppy breeds and names. Many local news stations, such as Live 5 News WCSC, WJXT News4JAX, and WFXRtv.com, are encouraging viewers to share photos and videos of their puppies, and CBS Boston is celebrating with a feature on Izzy the dog.

name: Peter Angelos
summary: Peter Angelos, the longtime owner of the Baltimore Orioles baseball team, passed away at the age of 94. Angelos was a prominent figure in Major League Baseball, best known for his tenure with the Orioles and his role in the 1994-95 Major League Baseball strike. He was also renowned for his legal career, where he made a name for himself as a crusader for the underdog. Angelos's leadership and commitment to the Baltimore community left a lasting impact on the city and the Orioles organization.
